message.content:
cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) network and channel state information (CSI) which are related to information theory. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper considers a downlink single-cell network with mixed multicast and unicast traffic scenario. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the quality of service (QoS) of the multicast traffic and investigates the performance of partial CSI. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a potential category as the paper deals with multicast and unicast streaming. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also possible as the paper evaluates the secrecy unicast throughput performance.
